"""
Noise Scaling Strategies on CIFAR-10
=====================================
Head-to-head comparison of three principled noise scaling methods
for SNN training, plus controls.

Strategies:
  A) FIXED:     noise_std = constant (current approach, baseline)
  B) THRESHOLD: noise_std = α × threshold (decision-boundary relative)
  C) SIGNAL:    noise_std = α × sqrt(BN running_var) (signal-relative)
  D) LEARNED:   noise_std = exp(learnable_param) per layer (network decides)
  E) CONTROL:   noise_std = 0 (no noise)

Each strategy swept across α values where applicable.
All tested on CIFAR-10 with identical conv-SNN architecture.

Run: Google Colab, GPU runtime. ~2-3 hours.
"""

import torch
import torch.nn as nn
import torch.nn.functional as F
from torch.utils.data import DataLoader
